# Default home-ephemeral list.
#
# Known cache/temp payloads are mounted as tmpfs by compose so host-side
# runtime/home stays literal and does not contain broken symlinks.
#
# Users can add more entries in /state/home-ephemeral.local. Each non-comment
# line has this format:
#   <home-relative-path> <target>
#
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
# Example:
#   .continue/cache /cache/continue
#
# Reserved home paths are rejected by the entrypoint (.zshrc, .zshenv, .profile,
# .bashrc, .bash_profile, .local/bin) so a bad list cannot rewrite the shell
# startup chain.
